<section xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xml:id="sec-1-2-lim">
  <title>The notion of limit</title>
  <objectives>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <p>
          Determine the limit of a function at a point using graphical, numerical, and algebraic methods.
        </p>
      </li>

      <li>
        <p>
          Explain how average velocity and instantaneous velocity are connected using the notion of limit.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </objectives>
  <outcomes>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <p>
            Algebra: factoring, multiplying out, common denominator, rationalizing
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            Graphs: holes and jumps
          </p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </outcomes>

  

